      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; SQA controls provide sufficient protection against use error at this risk level.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment beyond SQA controls (version control, archived scripts, peer review of boundary condition setup) is not required at MRL 2. The SQA programme documented under the Software Quality Assurance factor provides adequate coverage."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The constitutive hemolysis model and turbulence closure must be justified against available literature and validation data; model form uncertainty must be qualitatively bounded.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the standard form used in FDA-recognised CFD hemolysis studies. SST k-omega is appropriate for the transitional-to-turbulent regime in centrifugal pumps. The PCE-based UQ campaign (VR-04) quantified that hemolysis model coefficients contribute 22 % of total RHI variance, representing the dominant epistemic uncertainty source. This is acknowledged and bounded; no alternative model form was required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Boundary conditions and material properties must be derived from traceable clinical or experimental sources; input uncertainty ranges must be documented.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds are drawn from the COU operating matrix, traceable to clinical CPB protocols. Blood viscosity and hematocrit distributions are parameterised from published clinical data (mean ± 2 SD). All input uncertainty ranges were used as the basis for the 256-sample LHS UQ campaign (VR-04). Sobol indices confirm that the two most influential inputs (rotational speed and flow rate) are well-characterised. Input documentation satisfies MRL 2 requirements."
    },
