    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1. Grid convergence error is bounded below 5 %, experimental comparison satisfies the acceptance criterion at 4 of 5 operating points with conservative over-prediction at the fifth, and the UQ campaign (documented in VR-04 and embedded in factor rationales) confirms that dominant uncertainty sources are characterised and bounded. The CFD model is assessed as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device under the stated COU. Decision: Accepted.",
